<!--19-->Bred for Battle<br />
<!--36-->Spies of Saruman x3    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">If you don&#39;t know how to play this deck, or anything close to it you&#39;ve been living under a rock the past few months and have missed just about everything.  So I won&#39;t go into huge amounts of detail, here&#39;s the jist of the deck -<br />
<br />
Drop companions, move a lot.<br />
Drop Uruks, make them stop.<br />
<br />
You get Aragorn and Boromir ready to go and with Archery and some good ally help, you can keep Frodo alive for the end, and if need be slaughter their fellowship.  The Free Peoples side is chock full of things to keep frodo around, like his weapon, 8 other guys to die for him + thrarin, elves to shoot people, men to cut people, and plenty of healing from his signet buddies.  The main weakness is Enquea and big fierce Uruks off Savagery, so if you know either of those decks will be in your way play cautious.<br />
<br />
The Shadow side is designed to slow the opponenet down, and if need be beat them.  Lurtz isn&#39;t too important, the best minion is the Troop of Uruk-Hai who gets around all those nifty toys and has plenty of Vitality to soak up archery or what not.  The rest are cheap and Enquea is there for decks just like mine....kill of Legolas first, then Boromir, then whatever.  If you have the oppourtunity, set it up so that whoever fights your Uruk will die, and use the pumps when needed.  With a wounded fellowship, a couple Uruks, and a few twilight left it&#39;s almost suicide to move again.<br />
<br />
I think that about covers it, and for those on here that like to give bad reviews because &quot;it&#39;s not original&quot; please don&#39;t do that, because I&#39;d like criticism not stupid remarks.<br />
<br />
Thanks! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
